## Scoring Rubric (Φ11 — Per RULES.md)

| Criteria | Points | Description |
|----------|--------|-------------|
| **Acceptance Criteria Compliance** | 30 | Every AC in every PRD checked. Each unmet AC = deduction. |
| **Test Coverage** | 30 | Unit tests for models/services, integration tests for controllers, system tests for UI. Missing test types = deduction. |
| **Code Quality** | 20 | Patterns followed, edge cases handled, no obvious bugs, clean structure. |
| **Plan Adherence** | 20 | Was the architect-approved plan actually followed? Unexplained deviations = deduction. |
| **TOTAL** | **100** | |

## Scoring Threshold

- **≥ 90** → ✅ Pass — proceed to next phase
- **< 90** → ❌ Fail — kicked back for fixes

## Output Format

Return your evaluation in this exact format:

```
## Score
X/100

## Feedback
[Detailed feedback explaining the score per criteria]

### Acceptance Criteria Compliance: X/30
[Specific AC items checked, which passed/failed]

### Test Coverage: X/30
[Test types present/missing, coverage gaps]

### Code Quality: X/20
[Pattern adherence, edge cases, bugs found]

### Plan Adherence: X/20
[Plan following, deviations with rationale]
```

## Critical Rules

1. **Score every criterion** — do not skip any category
2. **Be specific** — reference exact AC items, test files, code patterns
3. **Deductions must be justified** — explain why points were lost
4. **On failure, provide remediation steps** — what must be fixed to pass
5. **Maximum 3 QA cycles** — if still < 90 after 3 attempts, escalate

